 class="author_photo"><img src="http://s2.hubimg.com/u/8666493_50.jpg"   alt="conradofontanilla profile image" title="conradofontanilla profile image"/></div><p class="comment_meta"><strong>conradofontanilla&nbsp;</strong><span class='timestamp'>4 months ago  from Philippines <small>Hub Author</small> </span></p><div class="comment_body"><p class="">Dr. Salk and his team did not use the double blind randomized with control statistical design in the Salk vaccine trial. He regarded this method unethical for this purpose. He used the observation method. So there was no placebo. Dr. Jonas did not want that anyone with a supposed placebo would go home with only a lollipop in hand. She/he went home also protected from polio. As to the new polio outbreak, it should be explained by the present administration of CDC. My Hub is explicit as to its coverage: not the present one. I can only speculate: resistance to vaccination, incomplete coverage, defective vaccine manufacture. Thanks for the vote and sharing.</p><p class="">I have now second thoughts about my example of an artificial vaccine, beta blocker. Lately there had been some safety issues around it. You can read more from Dr. Mercola. It can induce bleeding in the lungs. I had a cousin who was treated for hypertension. He was confined in a hospital, pronounced treated and released to go home. At the hospital door he vomited blood and expired.</p><p class="">Conrado</p></div></div><div id="comment_tgt_2641467" class="more_comments"></div><form name="comment_14836707" id="comment_14836707" method="get" action="/xml/comment.php"><input type="hidden" name="mod_id" value="14836707" /><div id='formErrors_14836707' class='alert'><ul></ul></div><input type="hidden" name="authed" value="1"/><div class="commenter_anon"></div><div class="compose_comment"><textarea wrap="virtual" autocomplete="off" onfocus="jq('#comText_14836707').select();" id="comText_14836707" name="comText_14836707" rows="6"></textarea></div><div class="post">